Richard,<br><br>
Glad to see you back.  Takes guts to say your mind with the likes of us floating around.<br><br>
Have to agree that any man who can die for his country should be able to vote for his country.  No argument on this issue.  Also agree any man who refuses to fight for his country or support the fighting man in the rear shouldn't have certain rights.  Lucky for you Carter saw things differently.<br><br>
Richard I must disagree with some issues.  Definition of slavery not quite correct, conscription maybe with pay is better, and don't forget room and board, and what about those spiffy uniforms.  I never wanted a gun put in your ribs and sent to Nam to fight.  Shit you would have probably gotten yourself killed or worst yet a real soldier trying to save your ass.  Things have changed Richard.  I grew up thinking this kind of thing was treason.  Sorry, just my opinion.  Nothing was stopping you from serving in another capacity.  People always talk politics when they are scared shitless.  Nobody wants to die no matter what the greater good.  It just happens.<br><br>
When have we entered an international conflict when our freedom was threatened.  You think Japan attacked because they thought they could kick our ass.  Nope.  Wars of politicians are for economics, pure and simple.  So whats new.  Have you supported any of the humanitarian efforts which put our boys at risk.  To be consistent, I guess not.<br><br>
We don't always get our way and rarely are we allowed to do anything we want.  Lifes not that simple.  If everyone took that position our country would be flying a different flag.  Can't defend without trained fighting men.  Guard, reserves, coast guard, merchant marines.  Lots of ways to serve.<br><br>
Good luck Dick.  We all need to rationalize what we are and what we have done.  
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


